Drogon framework

Similer to **Java Spring Boot** and **C++ backend**, **Drogon** is one of the best frameworks to learn if you want to build modern web backends in C++. 
It is designed for **high-performance REST APIs and web services**. 

## What is Drogon?

Drogon is an **asynchronous C++17/20 web framework** for building:

* REST APIs
* HTTP/HTTPS servers
* WebSocket servers
* Microservices
* Database-backed web applications
* Authentication services

It is cross-platform and supports Linux, Windows, macOS, and BSD systems. 

## Key Features

* ✅ C++17/20 support
* ✅ Very high performance
* ✅ Asynchronous I/O
* ✅ Coroutine support (C++20)
* ✅ REST API routing
* ✅ WebSocket
* ✅ HTTPS (OpenSSL)
* ✅ JSON support
* ✅ File upload/download
* ✅ PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite
* ✅ Redis client
* ✅ ORM
* ✅ Middleware (filters)
* ✅ Plugin system
* ✅ Session and cookies support 

## Architecture

```
Client
   │
HTTP/HTTPS
   │
Router
   │
Controller
   │
Service Layer
   │
Repository / ORM
   │
Database
```

This is similar to Spring Boot:

| Spring Boot     | Drogon               |
| --------------- | -------------------- |
| Controller      | HttpController       |
| Service         | Service class        |
| Repository      | ORM/DbClient         |
| Filter          | Filter               |
| Configuration   | config.json          |
| Embedded Tomcat | Embedded HTTP server |

## Example

```cpp
app().registerHandler(
    "/hello",
    [](const HttpRequestPtr& req,
       std::function<void(const HttpResponsePtr&)>&& callback)
    {
        auto resp = HttpResponse::newHttpResponse();
        resp->setBody("Hello World");
        callback(resp);
    });
```

## Database Support

Drogon supports:

* PostgreSQL
* MySQL / MariaDB
* SQLite

Features include:

* Async queries
* Connection pooling
* Transactions
* ORM model generation
* Prepared statements 

## Performance

Drogon is widely recognized as one of the fastest C++ web frameworks. It uses non-blocking event loops (`epoll` on Linux, `kqueue` on BSD/macOS) and has performed very well in TechEmpower benchmarks.

